    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Cleaning,
        Inspection, and Tests - Rocker Arm Carrier
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="11">
        <title>Rocker Arm Carrier</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Rocker Arm and Fulcrum Disassembly</title>
            <figure id="e300580" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the rocker arm fulcrum bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove six bolts (M8 x 45) and fulcrum bolt spacer holding all the rocker arm fulcrums
                    to the rocker arm carrier. Remove fulcrums and rocker arms as assemblies.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300581" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Removing the end fulcrum plate and fulcrum bolt spacer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">End fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum bolt spacer</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="e300582" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Compressing the rocker arm clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disassembly and assembly of dual and single rocker arm fulcrum plates are similar.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To disassemble the rocker arm from the fulcrum plate; hold rocker arm and fulcrum plate
                    upside down in the palm of your hand. Push down on fulcrum plate against rocker arm (relieving force
                    on ball) while simultaneously pushing rocker away from ball and fulcrum plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300583" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the rocker arm</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm ball</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move the rocker off the ball, keeping the ball in the detent of the fulcrum plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300584" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Removing the rocker arm clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the rocker arm clip.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit air pressure
                        to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean all parts with a suitable solvent. Use filtered compressed air to dry parts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect each rocker arm pivot foot and corresponding valve bridge for pitting or
                    scuffing. Inspect each rocker arm ball and socket for scuffing. Replace rocker arms and valve
                    bridges as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect rocker arm post ball socket for excessive wear. Inspect bolts for thread damage.
                    Replace worn components as required.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Rocker Arm and Fulcrum Assembly</title>
            <figure id="e300585" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing a new rocker arm clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disassembly and assembly of dual and single rocker arm fulcrum plates are similar.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new rocker arm clip onto the fulcrum plate.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300586" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the rocker arm ball</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm ball</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the ball onto the fulcrum plate detent. Hold rocker arm upside down in your
                    palm.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300587" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08091.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the rocker arm clip</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm clip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press lower part of the rocker arm against the rocker arm clip, push up with your palm
                    and push the upper part of the rocker arm over the rocker arm ball. Check for freedom of movement of
                    rocker arm on the fulcrum plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300588" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08049.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Installing the end fulcrum and fulcrum bolt spacer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fulcrum bolt spacer</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="e300589" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08050.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing an end rocker fulcrum plate</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position each assembled end rocker fulcrum plate (intake or exhaust) with a fulcrum bolt
                    spacer onto rocker carrier assembly. Orient
                    <emph type="bold">E</emph>
                    and
                    <emph type="bold">I</emph>
                    fulcrum stamping face up. Install bolt (M8 x 45) into each fulcrum and tighten to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_292.xml" xrefid="E30005B">special torque
                        <xref refid="E30005B"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position each assembled dual fulcrum plate with two fulcrum bolt spacers onto rocker
                    carrier assembly. Orient
                    <emph type="bold">E</emph>
                    and
                    <emph type="bold">I</emph>
                    stamping face up. Install two bolts (M8 x 45) into each fulcrum and tighten to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_292.xml" xrefid="E30005B">special torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e300590" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D0836.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the cylinder head to rocker arm carrier gasket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new cylinder head to rocker arm carrier gasket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
